---
description: Supabase database, RLS, auth, and data-access safety rules
globs: supabase/**/*.sql,supabase/migrations/**,app/api/**/*,lib/**/*supabase*,lib/**/*db*,lib/**/*auth*,lib/**/*run*,lib/**/*participant*,app/**/*auth*,app/**/*run*,app/**/*participant*
alwaysApply: false
---

# Supabase DB and RLS

- Any DB schema change must include a migration in `supabase/migrations`.
- Never modify the production DB directly as a substitute for migrations.
- Preserve RLS safety; do not weaken policies without explicit approval.
- Never expose service role usage to client-side code.
- Keep run visibility and participant access safe.
- Consider indexes for new query patterns.
- Update TypeScript types and services when schema changes.
